    • Constructor Detail

      • Rental

        public Rental(User aUser,
              Movie aMovie)
        Constructs a rental of a movie to a user for a certain number of days.
        Parameters:
        aUser - User who is renting aMovie.
        aMovie - Movie that is rented.
        Throws:
        IllegalStateException - if the movie is already rented.
        NullPointerException - if not all input parameters where set.
        IllegalArgumentException - if the user is too young to see the movie, or the user has already rented the maximum rentable movies
        MovieRentalException - if the user is not old enough to rent the movie.

      • materializeRentalFromDB

        public static Rental materializeRentalFromDB(int id,
                                             User aUser,
                                             Movie aMovie,
                                             LocalDate aRentalDate)
        Constructs a rental of a movie to a user at a given date for a certain number of days.
        Parameters:
        id - the unique identification of this rental
        aUser - User who is renting aMovie.
        aMovie - Movie that is rented.
        aRentalDate - date of start of this rental.
        Returns:
        a newly initialized Rental object.
        Throws:
        NullPointerException - if not all input parameters where set.
        MovieRentalException - if the user is not old enough to rent the movie.
